element.name: EMS Personnel's Last Name
element.definition: The last name of the personnel.

element.name: EMS Personnel's First Name
element.definition: The first name of the personnel.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Middle Name/Initial
element.definition: The middle name or initial of the personnel.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Mailing Address
element.definition: The Street or PO Box of the personnel's mailing address.
element.v3Comment: For individuals living outside the USA the full address can be entered in the address line.

element.name: EMS Personnel's City of Residence
element.definition: The city of the personnel's mailing address.
element.v3Comment:
Based on GNIS Civil Code or Populated Place code.
GNIS Codes Website: http://geonames.usgs.gov/domestic/download_data.htm

element.name: EMS Personnel's State
element.definition: The state of the personnel's mailing address.
element.v3Comment:
Based on ANSI Code.
GNIS Codes Website: http://geonames.usgs.gov/domestic/download_data.htm

element.name: EMS Personnel's ZIP Code
element.definition: The ZIP code of the personnel's mailing address.
element.v3Comment:
Zip Codes Product Website: https://www.zipcodedownload.com/Products/Product/Z5Commercial/Standard/Overview/
Product: USA - 5-digit ZIP Code Database, Commercial Edition

element.name: EMS Personnel's Country
element.definition: The country of the personnel mailing address.
element.v3Comment:
Based on ANSI Code.
ANSI Country Codes (ISO 3166) Website: http://www.iso.org/iso/country_codes/iso_3166_code_lists.htm

element.name: EMS Personnel's Phone Number
element.definition: The phone number for the personnel.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Email Address
element.definition: The primary email address of the personnel.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Date of Birth
element.definition: The personnel's date of birth.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Gender
element.definition: The personnel's gender.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Race
element.definition: The personnel's race as defined by the OMB (US Office of Management and Budget).
element.v3Comment: OMB requirements are provided at: http://www.omhrc.gov/templates/browse.aspx?lvl=2&lvlID=172. A single multiple choice question methodology is being implemented to improve the completion of ethnicity information. Ethnicity (Version 2.1.1: D08_14) has been merged with this data element and retired.

choice.description: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander

element.name: EMS Personnel's Citizenship
element.definition: The documentation of the personnel's citizenship.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Highest Educational Degree
element.definition: The highest educational degree completed by the personnel.
element.v3Comment: Based on Census 2000 Educational Attainment Question.

choice.description: High School Graduate-Diploma or the Equivalent (GED)
Some College Credit, but Less than 1 Year
1 or More Years of College, No Degree
Professional Degree (i.e. MD, DDS, DVM, LLB, JD)

element.name: EMS Personnel's Degree Subject/Field of Study
element.definition: The area of the personnel's post high-school (post-secondary) degree.

choice.description: Area, Ethnic, Cultural, and Gender Studies
Health Professions and Related Clinical Sciences, Not Including Emergency Medical Services
Liberal Arts and Sciences, General Studies, and Humanities
Not Classified by Field of Study
Parks, Recreation, Leisure and Fitness Studies
Security and Protective Services, Not Including Fire Science

element.name: EMS Personnel's Motor Vehicle License Type
element.definition: The type of motor vehicle license (i.e. Class A, B, Pilot, etc.) of the EMS personnel.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Immunization Status
element.definition: The type of immunization status.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Immunization Year
element.definition: The year associated with each immunization type.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Foreign Language Ability
element.definition: The languages spoken (other than English) by the personnel with at least an elementary level of proficiency.
element.v3Changes: Added to better describe the EMS workforce.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Agency ID Number
element.definition: The local agency ID number for the personnel.
element.v3Comment: This is a local ID and not the ID associated with the state credential. This may be the same as the state credential ID depending on the state and local implementation. This should be a unique number and not reused.

element.name: EMS Personnel's State of Licensure
element.definition: The state of the certification/licensure ID number assigned to the personnel member.

element.name: EMS Personnel's State's Licensure ID Number
element.definition: The state's licensure/certification ID number for the personnel.

element.name: EMS Personnel's State EMS Certification Licensure Level
element.definition: The personnel's state EMS certification level.
element.v3Comment:
Added 2009 EMS Education Levels.
The category EMT-Intermediate includes EMS professionals with an “85” or “99” certification level.

element.name: EMS Personnel's State EMS Current Certification Date
element.definition: The date of the personnel's current EMS certification/licensure.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Initial State's Licensure Issue Date
element.definition: The date on which the EMS personnel's state's EMS certification/licensure was originally issued. This is the date of the first certification/licensure for the EMS level.
element.v3Comment: Clarified as the FIRST (original) certification/licensure date.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Current State's Licensure Expiration Date
element.definition: The date on which the EMS personnel's (highest) state EMS certification/licensure expires.

element.name: EMS Personnel's National Registry Number
element.definition: The National Registry number associated with the level of certification/licensure obtained through NREMT.

element.name: EMS Personnel's National Registry Certification Level
element.definition: The level of the current National Registry of Emergency Medical Technicians (NREMT) certification.
element.v3Comment: The category EMT-Intermediate includes EMS professionals with an “85” or “99” certification level.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Current National Registry Expiration Date
element.definition: The date on which the EMS Personnel's National Registry of EMTs certification/licensure expires

element.name: EMS Personnel's Employment Status
element.definition: The personnel's primary employment status for this agency.

choice.description: Neither an Employee Nor a Volunteer

element.name: EMS Personnel's Employment Status Date
element.definition: The personnel's employment status date.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Hire Date
element.definition: The date the employee was hired by the EMS agency for this current job.
element.v3Comment: This is intended to collect information based on the current employment/job. If the EMS personnel has a come and go status, this should reflect the most recent employment/job.

element.name: EMS Personnel's Primary EMS Job Role
element.definition: The individuals primary/main EMS role at the EMS agency. This is the function which is performed the majority of the time for the EMS personnel.
element.v3Comment: This is a single choice data element which should reflect the EMS Personnel's primary/main job role for which he/she functions. It is understood that most EMS personnel perform more than one role as a part of their position. Other roles should be documented in dPersonnel.36 (EMS Personnel's Other Job Responsibilities).

element.name: EMS Personnel's Other Job Responsibilities
element.definition: The EMS personnel's other job responsibilities at the agency beyond their primary role documented in dPersonnel.34 (EMS Personnel's Primary EMS Job Role).

element.name: EMS Personnel's Total Length of Service in Years
element.definition: The personnel's total length of EMS service at any level (years).

element.name: EMS Personnel's Date Length of Service Documented
element.definition: The date which the length of EMS service was documented.
element.v3Comment: Associated with dPersonnel.37 (EMS Personnel's Total Length of Service in Years).

element.name: EMS Professional's Practice Level
element.definition: The EMS certification level at which the individual is providing patient care services for the EMS agency.
element.v3Comment: The category EMT-Intermediate includes EMS professionals with an “85” or “99” certification level.

element.name: Date of Professional's Certification or Licensure for Agency
element.definition: The date that the Certification/Licensure was achieved for the local EMS agency.
